  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 0f3a2c8c7b8f4d9c9d5a3d11d5f50101, type: 3}
  m_Name: PokedexCrow
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  entryId: bird_crow
  commonName: American Crow
  scientificName: Corvus brachyrhynchos
  icon: {fileID: 2800000, guid: 8e5481a3ce647014c8df18fc9532d71b, type: 3}
  category: Bird
  habitat: Forest edges
  height: 40 - 53 cm
  weight: 31 - 62 g
  diet: Omnivore
  rarity: Very common
  shortDescription: A large, entirely black bird renowned for its problem-solving
    abilities and exceptional intelligence.
  behaviorNotes: Highly observant and cooperative. Flies at high altitudes over tree
    canopies and communicates with harsh "caw" sounds.
  observationTips: Often found perched on the very top branches of dead trees, surveying
    the surrounding forest landscape.
  funFact: Crows can recognize specific human faces, remember them for years, and
    communicate to their flock whether a person is a friend or a threat.
  facts:
  - They can construct custom hooks out of twigs or wire to pull food out of hard-to-reach
    crevices and narrow spaces.
  - Crows hold ritualistic gatherings around deceased flock members, gathering in
    trees to evaluate potential local threats.
  - Young crows often stay with their parents for several years to help raise and
    protect subsequent generations of chicks.
